is archive "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==========================================================

NAME
----

is archive - This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if

SYNOPSIS
--------

This [Conditional Tag](/Conditional_Tags "Conditional Tags") checks if
any type of Archive page is being displayed. An Archive is a
[Category](/Function_Reference/is_category "Function Reference/is category"),
[Tag](/Function_Reference/is_tag "Function Reference/is tag"),
[Author](/Function_Reference/is_author "Function Reference/is author")
or a [Date](/Function_Reference/is_date "Function Reference/is date")
based pages. This is a boolean function, meaning it returns either TRUE
or FALSE.

USAGE
-----

` <?php is_archive(); ?> `

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `(boolean)` 
:   True on success, false on failure.

EXAMPLES
--------

`  is_archive(); `

NOTES
-----

### Custom Post Types

is\_archive() does not accept any parameters. If you want to check if
this is the archive of a custom post type, use [is\_post\_type\_archive(
\$post\_type
)](http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/is_post_type_archive "http://codex.wordpress.org/Function_Reference/is_post_type_archive")

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: 1.5.0

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`is_archive()` is located in `wp-includes/query.php`.

